<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Using the "word" option type, eg</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$opts = new Zend_Console_Getopt(array(
    'foo|f=w' =&gt; 'Foo option, with required "word" parameter'
));
</code></pre>

<p>does not allow a hyphen to be present, eg</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
command --foo some-value-with-hyphens
</code></pre>

<p>This is due to the preg_match check in Zend_Console_Getopt::_checkParameterType() that checks for "/\W/" (anything other than letters, numbers and underscore) characters.</p>

<p>According to the documentation, the "w" flag should allow
bq. "=w" for a word parameter (a string containing no whitespace)</p>

<p>From <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.console.getopt.rules.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

